First, we need to find the symmetric difference (A △ B). The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets A or B, but not in their intersection.

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}
A ∩ B = {3, 4, 5}

Now subtract the intersection from the union:

A △ B = {1, 2, 6, 7}

Now we need to find the intersection of (A △ B) and {3, 4, 5}:

(A △ B) ∩ {3, 4, 5} = {}

The intersection is an empty set, as there are no common elements between (A △ B) and {3, 4, 5}.
